│ return false and do not perform runtime unrolling. I’ll implement a conservative guard by inspecting the BackedgeTakenCount SCEV, and if it is a SCEVUDivExpr/SDivExpr with RHS not      │
│ known nonzero, bail out. This avoids generating the problematic udiv sequence for this test.                                                                                             │
